# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# RESEND + SUPABASE AUTH SETUP  (one-time, in Supabase dashboard)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Supabase sends OTP emails via its built-in Auth system.
# Point it at Resend so emails arrive reliably:
#
# 1. Get a Resend API key from resend.com (free tier is fine for low volume)
#    Verify your sending domain in Resend (e.g. mail.dartvoice.com)
#
# 2. In Supabase dashboard:
#    Authentication → Settings → SMTP Provider → Enable custom SMTP
#      Host:     smtp.resend.com
#      Port:     465
#      Username: resend
#      Password: <your Resend API key>
#      Sender:   DartVoice <noreply@dartvoice.com>
#
# 3. Customise the OTP email template (optional):
#    Authentication → Email Templates → Magic Link / OTP
#    Subject: Your DartVoice sign-in code
#    Body:    Your sign-in code is: {{ .Token }}
#             It expires in 10 minutes.
#
# 4. Set OTP expiry (Authentication → Settings → OTP Expiry): 600 seconds
#
# That's it — billing.py calls supabase.auth.sign_in_with_otp()
# and Supabase+Resend handles delivery automatically.
